docs.lead_paragraph: Walt Frazier sat in his room at the Hotel New Yorker yesterday welcoming a day of complete rest. Since last Thursday, the New York Knickerbockers have beaten the Baltimore Bullets, the Eastern Division leaders in the National Basketball Association, once, and the Boston Celtics, the defending champions, twice as part of a five-game winning streak they will carry against the Atlanta Hawks tonight at Madison Square Garden.
